The aims of the course are to promote students’ interest in Canoeing. Upon the completion of the course, students should be able to :
1. achieve the basic skills of canoeing;
2. master the rescuing and rolling techniques;
3. develop the interest in canoeing.

The aims of the course are to promote students’ interest in the sport of snorkel diving and to encourage attainment and appreciation of good performance standards in snorkel diving. Upon completion of the course, students should be able to:

1. demonstrate knowledge of the related skills; 
2. refine the fundamental skill of snorkel diving; 
3. demonstrate knowledge of the sport as well as safety; 
4. improve the participants’ state of fitness through the sport.

The aims of the course are to promote students’ interest in swimming and to encourage attainment and appreciation of good performance standards in swimming. Upon the completion of the course, students should be able to:

1. perform the basic stroke of breast stroke;
2. develop confidence in swimming;
3. perform several type of recreational swimming.

The aims of the course are to promote students’ interest in social dance and to enhance their social skill. Upon completion of the course, students should be able to:
1. demonstrate good ballroom etiquette; 
2. demonstrate knowledge of the basic steps: some variations, styles of waltz, cha-cha-cha and rock’n roll; 
3. develop sense of rhythm, body control, balance and an appreciation of development and form.

The aims of this course are to promote health and aerobic fitness through participation in aerobic dance, to arouse students’ awareness of healthy lifestyle and to enhance their quality of life. Upon completion of the course, students should be able to:
1. achieve or maintain a good state of cardiovascular fitness; 
2. enhance muscle toning and possess good body alignment; 
3. employ good eating habit.

The aim of the course are to introduce and promote students’ interest in aquatic fitness and to understand training benefits gained from this activity.  Upon completion of the course, students should be able to:
1. know the general concept of Physical Fitness and continue their fitness programme after the course; 
2. improve cardiorespiratory fitness by exercising aerobically at an intensity of 70% - 85% maximal heart rate reserved;
3. increase adequate and specific flexibility by performing stretching exercises to their fullest range of motion;
4. increase adequate and specific muscular strength after performing muscle toning exercises;
5. enhance the sense of rhythm after the course.

The aims of the course are to improve students' skill in Physical Fitness through lectures and participate in various fitness activities. Upon completion of the course, student should be able to:
1. understand the general concept of physical Fitness;
2. know the ways to improve fitness;
3. use the fitness equipment/machines in the Physical Fitness Room;

The aims of the course are to introduce and promote students’ interest in step aerobic dancing and to understand training benefits gained from this activity. Upon completion of the course, student should be able to:
1. know the general concept of Physical Fitness and continue their fitness program after the course;  
2. improve cardiorespiratory fitness by exercising aerobically at an intensity of 70%-85% maximal heart rate served; 
3. increase adequate and specific flexibility by performing stretching exercises to their fullest range of motion; 
4. increase adequate and specific muscular strength after performing muscle toning exercises; 
5. enhance the sense of rhythm after the course.

The aims of this course are to promote health and fitness through exercising with fitballs, to arouse students’ attention on cardiovascular fitness, muscle toning, flexibility and postural awareness so as to enhance their quality of life. Upon completion of the course, students should be able to:
1. develop the skills of exercising on the fitball; 
2. achieve or maintain a good state of cardiovascular fitness; 
3. enhance muscle toning and possess good body alignment; 
4. improve their state of flexibility

The aims of this course are to promote health and fitness through performing Yoga, to arouse students’ attention on postural awareness, muscular fitness and balance so as to enhance their quality of life. Upon the completion of the course, students should be able to:
1. perform not less than 10 Yoga exercises on their own; 
2. achieve or maintain a good state of wellness, both body and mind; 
3. enhance muscular strength and endurance so as to possess good body alignment; 
4. improve their state of flexibility.

The aims of this course are to promote health and fitness through performing Yoga, to arouse students’ attention on postural awareness, muscular fitness and balance so as to enhance their quality of life. Upon the completion of the course, students should be able to:
1. perform a sequence of at least 10 Yoga exercises on their own; 
2. achieve or maintain a good state of wellness, both body and mind; 
3. enhance muscular strength and endurance so as to possess good body alignment; 
4. improve their state of flexibility.

The aim of the course is mainly to promote students’ concept of applying Tai Chi principle of human movements to enhance the joy of running.  Based upon posture alignment and relaxation in terms of the Tai Chi principle, Needle in the Cotton, students will run pain-free and with less effort.  As the enjoyment of running naturally increases, students will turn running as their lifelong practice.
Upon completion of the course, students should be able to:


apply the knowledge of Tai Chi principle in running practice ; 
demonstrate the main four skills of Chi Running: posture, ankle lift & Chi Walking, lean and arm swing; 
demonstrate relaxation with Chi Running Looseners, Tai Chi exercise, belly and nasal breathing; 
demonstrate how to use metronome to identify optimal cadence, running gears and stride length; 
demonstrate Tai Chi drills to enhance engagement of core muscles and feeling of Dantien.

The aims of the course are to introduce the basic skills and knowledge of foil fencing and to promote students’ interest and pleasure in participation.  Upon completion of the course, students should be able to:
1. name and identify the equipment and correct clothing necessary for foil fencing; 
2. observe the safety measures in foil fencing; 
3. demonstrate knowledge and understanding of the basic skills of foil fencing through the application in practical situation; 
4. demonstrate understanding and application of the basic rules and scoring of foil fencing; 
5. develop an appreciation of the game of foil fencing.

The aims of the course are to promote students' interest in golf, and to encourage attainment and appreciation of good performance standards in golf. Upon the completion of the course, students should be able to:
1.   be aware of the basic safety measures of the full swing at beginner's level; 
2.   practice their swing with a No.7 and/or No.5 iron; 
3.   demonstrate a proper etiquette on playing golf.

